title: For Sale/Trade:  Romanian AK-47 Lancaster Arms Rifle up for sale or possible trade
postcontent:
Up for sale or possible trade is a Beautiful example of an AK-47 Rifle which I purchased 4 years ago from a individual down in Columbus Ga. Since I've never shot this rifle and it has been strictly a safe queen. I wanted to share his exact description of this AK when I bought it. 
I'm selling one of my favorite toys, my Lancaster AK-47. This is a Romanian AK, but it's not a cheap lowly WASR, these are built on American receivers w/G2 trigger group from the Romanian "G Models" (G stands for Guardia' and were the genuine military issue rifles.) I am the original owner of this rifle, purchasing it new about 8 years ago, directly from Lancaster Arms in Arizona (and shipped directly to Columbus.)
At that time Lancaster was very highly regarded by AK aficionados, but as order volume increased, they ability to maintain the same quality began to suffer after a few years, as did their reputation.
But the older Lancasters are still widely considered excellent rifles, as this one definitely is. One of the cool production trademarks was that they Parkerized the bare metal, and then used that as a base for the Gun-Kote baked on epoxy finish that looks great and is completely corrosion resistant.
The rifle has only been fired a few times, and is in pristine condition. The chrome bore is clean and crisp. The front sites and gas tube are perfectly straight, and the rivet heads are perfectly formed, and magazines fit firmly (like I said, it ain't a WASR). I installed an ERGO-Grip myself, as the are much more comfortable and ergonomic than those cheesy stock AK grips. I also installed the larger, Bulgarian flash-hider seen in the pics. The rifle has both the cleaning rod and cleaning kit concealed in the butt-stock.
Included is the green-web AK sling, Case, 2 mags and one (1) Russian (Tula) Bake-Lite magazine as seen in the photos ( These are expensive, difficult to find and collector items on their own). 

I'm asking $1,500.00 or best cash offer. But may consider a trade for an AR-10 or Kimber Crimson 1911 45 pistol or what do you have? You can text me at 404-427-133one if you have any interest. Please don't waste my time if you are not legally allowed to own this firearm.

title: For Sale:  MODEL 1873 CHAMELOT-DELVIGNE ORDNANCE REVOLVER - 11mm
postcontent:
Beautiful French Chamelot- Dilvigne Model 1873 Revolver chambered in 11 mm french.

The gun is a 98% numbers matching example including the internal parts.
The dis-assembly screw located in front on the cylinder is an original replacement.
I ordered it from a french mil-surp supplier. Age appropriate with a matching finish.

The F block stamping dates the gun between 1873-1876 & its has a F138XX serial number.
The gun has two P stamps & S1892 stamping that indicate it was re-barreled in 1892.
It's one of the 1st DA/SA guns made and one of the 1st center fire guns made.
The markings indicate a manufacture date of 1873 (the first year of production)
It wasn't issued until 1874 and there were approx. 337,081 made.

Still retains the factory "Bright" or bare metal finish. Gunsmith advised it appeared original.
Bore is in excellent condition with sharp rifling & no apparent erosion or damage. 
The trigger & hammer still have the correct "straw" coloring. Very minimal signs of usage.
Handle may have been refinished??? However there no cracks/chips. 
The checkering is very deep & the finish still retains a shine. 
The Gun looks great to be 139 yrs old!!
There is a little patina on the bottom of the handle & minor age blemishes throughout.

A gunsmith advised it appeared mechanically sound but I have never fired the gun.
The cylinder aligns perfectly with the barrel & the Lock up/Timing are very tight.
The Double Action & Single Action trigger pull are extremely smooth. 

Ammo can be ordered at:
www.gadcustomcartridges.com/

Link to American Rifleman that contains some detailed info of the gun:
http://www.americanrifleman.org/articles/2012/10/17/french-model-1873-revolver/

Dating info link (available on other sites as well)
http://britishmilitariaforums.yuku.com/sreply/77721/French-Revolver

Asking $425 OBO. I will consider modern firearm related trades & reasonable cash offers.

title: For Sale/Trade:  Blueprinted Remington 700 .308 5R Rock Creek barreled action
postcontent:
For your consideration is a blueprinted Remington 700 chambered in .308.  The action has been squared and trued center to bore; the inner tenon was opened up .010" and new threads were single point cut center to bore.  The actions lugs have also been squared and trued.  The bolt lugs, as well as the bolt nose and face have been trued and squared.  All machine work is done on a precision lathe with a single point cuter all center to bore.  Both the action and bolt are dial indicated to .0001" before any work is performed.  For this build the bolt was also spiral fluted.

A brand new Rock Creek stainless match grade 5R rifing barrel was used for this build.  The contour is an M24 heavy bull barrel with 11.27 twist and finished at 24".  An ovedsized Badger Ordinance recoil lug was installed to give a longer barrel shank.  The barrel threads were also single point cut and hand fit to this action.  The breech was cut to .0035" and the headspace was cut to .0015".  This is much tighter than factory specs and will lead to a much more accurate shooter.  The barrel was crowned with an 11 degree target crown.  The barrel has only 3 rounds through her...  I have plenty of pics to share showing the machine work being completed.

Once the machine work was completed and the rifle test fired the barreled action was left in the white but this rifle can still be customized to your needs - add a muzzle brake; cerakote finish; detachable mag; ect. 

The barreled action in a quality stock will easily shoot 1/2 MOA with factory ammo and is capable of 1/4 MOA using hand loaded ammo.  I have a few HS precision stocks and a few Bell and Carlson stocks to offer with this build.

I have a few other blueprinted Rem 700s avalible as well so if you have another caliber in mind send a note...  I probally have it or can build it.

Will ship to your FFL if needed.
